# California Revenue & Taxation Code Section 17052(g)
# CalEITC Inflation Adjustment
#
# Source: https://leginfo.legislature.ca.gov/faces/codes_displaySection.xhtml?sectionNum=17052.&lawCode=RTC

text: """
(g)(1) For each taxable year beginning on or after January 1, 2016, the
Franchise Tax Board shall recompute the amounts in subdivision (b) in the
same manner as provided in subdivision (h) of Section 17041.

(g)(2) The changes made by subdivision (a) of Section 2 of the act adding
this subdivision shall apply to taxable years beginning on or after
January 1, 2018. For the 2018 taxable year, the percentage change figure
furnished pursuant to paragraph (1) of subdivision (h) of Section 17041
shall be increased by 7 percent. For the 2019 taxable year, that percentage
change figure shall be increased by 3 percent.
"""

# This subsection establishes that CalEITC thresholds are indexed
# using the same CA CPI methodology as RTC 17041(h)
# Indexed values are published in FTB Form 3514 instructions annually
